scene.message:
President: Phew... that was{nl}
close, that was close.{waitkey}{clearbox}Man, I got in a fight and{nl}
nearly got nabbed by the vice{nl}
principal — almost got a{nl}
lecture.{waitkey}{clearbox}Well, they won't find me here.{waitkey}{ret}

President: You all work hard,{nl}
too. Leave this place to me,{nl}
the president, and just do{nl}
your very best.{waitkey}{ret}

Drama Member: This is about{nl}
when Ms. Saeko was in the{nl}
drama club.{waitkey}{clearbox}I've heard she fought with{nl}
her best friend over the role{nl}
of the Snow Queen.{waitkey}{clearbox}I forget the surname, but it{nl}
was a Tomomi, I think. Ms.{nl}
Saeko cried when she told it.{waitkey}{ret}

Drama Member: The Snow Queen's{nl}
mask has so much sad history{nl}
behind it.{waitkey}{clearbox}When the town's back to{nl}
normal, maybe I'll make that{nl}
story into a play.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Is our drama club{nl}
good enough to win{nl}
competitions?{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: For the sake of the{nl}
three who guarded the tower{nl}
too, let's hurry and go beat{nl}
the Night Queen.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Cramped room~ It's{nl}
kinda like being inside a{nl}
huge refrigerator~{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: That council prez!{nl}
The thought of a guy like{nl}
that running the school makes{nl}
me so mad!{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: So this room's packed{nl}
with the aroma of sweat and{nl}
tears from maidens who gave{nl}
their youth to theater?{waitkey}What do we do, huh?!{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: I wonder if a TV{nl}
station's dressing room is{nl}
like this. I'd love to go~{waitkey}{ret}
